  "text": "It was shown in [CITATION_1] that every ϕ ∈ S m induces a bounded composition operator on each of the spaces H 2 m,β , satisfying a \"one-variable style\" norm estimate, in particular an estimate which depends only on the value of ϕ at 0. In fact when m = 1 this is precisely the \"classical\" norm estimate for composition operators on the standard scale of Hilbert function spaces. In higher dimensions, a related upper bound was obtained by Bayart [4, Theorem 4.1], which applies to certain univalent mappings (not necessarily in S m ) but which depends both on ϕ(0) and on global estimates for derivatives of ϕ. ",
  "correct_citation": {
